 <text>
  <front>
   <head>I Look Into My Glass</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+-+-+">I look into my glass,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+-+">And view my wasting skin,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+++-+-+">And say, Would God it came to pass</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+-+-+">My heart had shrunk as thin!"</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+-+-+">For then, I, undistrest</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+++-+">By hearts grown cold to me,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+-+-+">Could lonely wait my endless rest</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+">With equanimity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+-+-+">But Time to make me grieve,</l>
     <l n="10" met="++-+-+">Part steals, lets part abide;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+-+-+-+">And shakes this fragile frame at eve</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+--++">With throbbings of noontide.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
